<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-11-30T10:49:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-11-30T10:49:00-05:00" n="635" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d635">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 711.38/56.</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Port au Prince</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-11-30T11:00:00-04:49">
                                    <hi rend="italic">November 30, 1915—11 a.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Commission with full powers, in accordance with your November 12,
                            appointed: Solon Ménos, Haitian Minister at Washington, President;
                            Auguste Magloire, administrator of finance, Port au Prince, and Pierre
                            Hudicourt, lawyer and plenipotentiary to second peace conference at the
                            Hague, members. Commission expects to leave this week.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Blanchard.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>